                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114 Pacific War/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Huddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-24">February 24,
                            1942</date>.<lb/>[Received February 24—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>732. American interests—Japan. Swiss Legation Tokyo telegraphs February 17 report
                    as follows in response to Department’s 86, January 13, paragraphs 1, 2, 3 and
                        3<hi rend="italic">c</hi>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Japanese Government replies in substance ‘regarding paragraphs 1, 2, 3,
                            it has notified Intercroixrouge<note n="35" xml:id="d684fn35"
                                >International Committee of the Red Cross.</note> of its agreement
                            exchange <pb facs="0811" n="799" xml:id="pg_799"/> information
                            concerning prisoners and internees and also for establishment official
                            information bureau for prisoners of war’; as for paragraph 4 (3<hi
                                rend="italic">c</hi>) Japanese Foreign Office refers to note
                            communicated by my telegram January 30 (see Legation’s 398, February 4).
                            [”]</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
